WEBVTT

1
00:00:49.426 --> 00:00:50.506
There. there. it's nothing.

2
00:00:52.429 --> 00:00:53.429
They're just ants.

3
00:07:39.586 --> 00:07:42.631
Good afternoon. everyone.
Thank you for being here.

4
00:07:42.714 --> 00:07:45.884
Ernesto and I are so
pleased that you can join us

5
00:07:45.967 --> 00:07:50.263
for our 5th Gala fundraiser
of the Walasa Foundation.

6
00:07:54.809 --> 00:07:58.230
We are continuing to make a difference
in the lives of so many children

7
00:07:58.313 --> 00:08:01.024
suffering from violence
in rural Colombia.

8
00:08:01.107 --> 00:08:02.107
Thank you very much.

9
00:08:05.528 --> 00:08:06.780
"Despite progress.

10
00:08:06.863 --> 00:08:10.867
poverty and hunger are on the
rise in many parts of Colombia.

11
00:08:10.951 --> 00:08:16.873
Since we began. The Walasa Foundation
has helped nourish hundreds of children.

12
00:08:16.957 --> 00:08:21.628
Supplying meals in areas where
previously there were none.

13
00:08:21.711 --> 00:08:26.091
And we continue to fight to
provide relief to the little ones."

14
00:08:27.259 --> 00:08:28.510
General.

15
00:08:29.177 --> 00:08:31.054
Thank you for inviting me.

16
00:08:32.097 --> 00:08:33.472
But why am I here?

17
00:08:33.557 --> 00:08:36.058
It's part of my job to mingle
with these people. Pereira.

18
00:08:37.018 --> 00:08:38.937
You are here to keep
me from killing them.

19
00:08:41.523 --> 00:08:43.858
Don't complain. At
least the food is good.

20
00:08:45.944 --> 00:08:47.195
General.

21
00:08:53.118 --> 00:08:55.495
May I please speak with
the Colonel for a moment?

22
00:09:49.591 --> 00:09:50.592
General.

23
00:09:51.092 --> 00:09:52.093
General.

24
00:09:52.802 --> 00:09:54.596
Thank you for coming.

25
00:09:55.388 --> 00:09:57.241
I'm sorry we didn't get a
chance to speak tonight.

26
00:09:57.265 --> 00:10:01.353
I would like to discuss the
shooting in Ciudad Bolívar.

27
00:10:01.436 --> 00:10:03.539
You should talk to the Narcotics
Unit. I'm not involved.

28
00:10:03.563 --> 00:10:05.899
Nevertheless. I would
like to hear your opinion.

29
00:10:05.982 --> 00:10:07.525
I'm sorry. I don't think so.

30
00:10:07.609 --> 00:10:09.444
Is that an official
"no comment?"

31
00:10:10.487 --> 00:10:12.697
Listen. I really appreciate
your charitable spirit.

32
00:10:12.781 --> 00:10:13.781
But I know who you are.

33
00:10:14.950 --> 00:10:17.786
And I know. you have been treated
better here than in your own country.

34
00:10:17.869 --> 00:10:20.038
I'm sure you'd want
to keep it that way.

35
00:10:21.081 --> 00:10:22.374
Excuse me.

36
00:10:33.677 --> 00:10:36.763
This is Violeta Matíz. and
this is "Bogotá Revealed."

37
00:10:36.846 --> 00:10:37.847
on 103.1 F.M.

38
00:10:39.307 --> 00:10:42.852
Many times on this show
we have talked about war

39
00:10:42.936 --> 00:10:45.146
and the terrible toll it
has taken on our country.

40
00:10:46.106 --> 00:10:48.942
And while the war may
be officially over.

41
00:10:49.025 --> 00:10:51.361
there is still violence.

42
00:10:51.444 --> 00:10:56.866
I want to talk about an American woman
who was recently abducted outside Bogotá.

43
00:10:57.784 --> 00:10:58.910
Amber Chesborough.

44
00:10:59.411 --> 00:11:04.249
Her brother Alex joins me in
the studio to deliver a message.

45
00:11:04.332 --> 00:11:07.752
as we have done on many
occasions on "Kidnapped Voices."

46
00:11:09.004 --> 00:11:12.674
I'll turn it over to her brother
so he can speak to her directly.

47
00:12:07.562 --> 00:12:10.482
No. this is not good. It's shit.

48
00:12:11.650 --> 00:12:14.527
We're losing control
of the narrative.

49
00:12:22.118 --> 00:12:24.454
I'd like to send a
message to the kidnappers…

50
00:12:24.537 --> 00:12:27.165
I'm here if you want
to speak with me.

51
00:12:27.249 --> 00:12:28.249
To listen to you

52
00:12:29.292 --> 00:12:30.502
without any conditions

53
00:12:31.294 --> 00:12:34.256
to deliver whatever message
you want to send to the world.

54
00:12:35.006 --> 00:12:37.551
Let's tell the boss
to bring that bitch.

55
00:13:08.123 --> 00:13:09.332
What's wrong?

56
00:13:09.416 --> 00:13:11.459
Why don't we let
the American go?

57
00:13:12.460 --> 00:13:16.047
I just think this whole
plan could get us killed.

58
00:13:17.048 --> 00:13:18.128
That's not going to happen.

59
00:13:18.550 --> 00:13:21.845
We have the advantage and have
worked too hard for this opportunity.

60
00:13:24.014 --> 00:13:25.932
It's crazy to bring
a journalist here

61
00:13:26.016 --> 00:13:27.118
to the middle of the jungle.

62
00:13:27.142 --> 00:13:28.142
I don't see the point.

63
00:13:32.522 --> 00:13:34.608
Relax. When we get to Venezuela.

64
00:13:34.691 --> 00:13:38.862
the SEBIN will put
an altar for us.

65
00:13:38.945 --> 00:13:40.280
They will kiss our feet.

66
00:13:40.363 --> 00:13:41.573
And that's what you want?

67
00:13:41.656 --> 00:13:43.408
I want respect!

68
00:13:44.409 --> 00:13:45.409
Wonderful.

69
00:13:46.411 --> 00:13:48.163
Poetic.

70
00:13:52.125 --> 00:13:56.922
To be able to hold an American
hostage is the ultimate.

71
00:13:57.547 --> 00:14:01.134
It shows that we are strong
and the government is weak.

72
00:14:01.218 --> 00:14:03.720
And to be able to
break that illusion

73
00:14:04.471 --> 00:14:06.932
of a powerful and
authoritarian government.

74
00:14:07.015 --> 00:14:09.559
It legitimizes us as a
revolutionary movement.

75
00:14:09.643 --> 00:14:11.895
And it makes people think.

76
00:14:11.978 --> 00:14:16.149
"The government must be very weak if
it can't save one fucking American."

77
00:14:22.322 --> 00:14:25.116
Once that idea gets
planted like a seed.

78
00:14:26.117 --> 00:14:27.994
another one grows.

79
00:14:28.745 --> 00:14:32.415
"If the government is that
bad. we have to change it."

80
00:14:32.499 --> 00:14:37.546
That's what we are doing.
giving hope to our people.

81
00:14:55.814 --> 00:14:58.483
- Trust me.
- When have I ever not trusted you?

82
00:14:59.859 --> 00:15:00.986
I love you.

83
00:15:02.654 --> 00:15:03.655
Manipulator.

84
00:15:14.082 --> 00:15:16.418
For you. Hurry!

85
00:15:17.502 --> 00:15:18.503
Move.

86
00:16:08.845 --> 00:16:10.138
The Comandante is waiting.

87
00:16:15.560 --> 00:16:17.979
Don't make him angry.

88
00:16:24.110 --> 00:16:25.737
Pleasure to meet you.

89
00:16:26.821 --> 00:16:27.989
The pleasure is mine.

90
00:16:28.073 --> 00:16:30.700
Did you have a good trip?

91
00:16:30.784 --> 00:16:32.911
You must be exhausted.

92
00:16:32.994 --> 00:16:35.163
Would you like
some food or water?

93
00:16:35.247 --> 00:16:37.040
Or rest for a while?

94
00:16:37.123 --> 00:16:38.625
I'm fine.

95
00:16:38.708 --> 00:16:40.335
Sit.

96
00:16:47.634 --> 00:16:49.553
You know this is
a mistake. right?

97
00:16:50.178 --> 00:16:51.846
And it will end badly.

98
00:16:53.598 --> 00:16:55.016
The mistake is theirs.

99
00:16:55.767 --> 00:16:57.519
They thought they
were untouchable.

100
00:16:59.229 --> 00:17:01.231
And if this turns out bad. well.

101
00:17:01.314 --> 00:17:03.108
these are risks we
take during war.

102
00:17:03.191 --> 00:17:05.651
If you really want to
teach a lesson. let her go.

103
00:17:06.319 --> 00:17:08.112
Nobody wants to
return to the past.

104
00:17:09.447 --> 00:17:14.160
Some people do want another
war and we'll give it to them.

105
00:17:14.244 --> 00:17:16.787
If you release her. I'll
write a nice story about you.

106
00:17:17.789 --> 00:17:18.622
I would like that.

107
00:17:18.707 --> 00:17:22.960
But that's a bit too romantic
for things to end up that way.

108
00:17:23.044 --> 00:17:24.379
What are your goals?

109
00:17:25.088 --> 00:17:26.089
Who are you?

110
00:17:27.215 --> 00:17:28.216
I'm just a man.

111
00:17:29.426 --> 00:17:32.053
Trying to create
a new atmosphere.

112
00:17:32.137 --> 00:17:33.597
A new mentality.

113
00:17:34.180 --> 00:17:36.182
And these are my friends.

114
00:17:38.310 --> 00:17:39.352
Talk to her.

115
00:17:40.687 --> 00:17:42.188
Tell me what you think.

116
00:17:43.690 --> 00:17:44.690
Think about what?

117
00:17:45.984 --> 00:17:47.777
Whether or not she is CIA.

118
00:17:48.403 --> 00:17:49.988
You think she will tell me?

119
00:17:50.780 --> 00:17:53.033
Find out. You can do it.

120
00:17:54.034 --> 00:17:55.076
Go ahead.

121
00:17:55.869 --> 00:17:56.870
Okay.

122
00:17:57.621 --> 00:17:59.372
Give me some time
with her. I'll try.

123
00:17:59.915 --> 00:18:01.666
Let's get ready to move.

124
00:20:28.730 --> 00:20:30.232
Time's up.

125
00:21:03.056 --> 00:21:04.724
Here she is.

126
00:21:04.808 --> 00:21:05.976
Come here.

127
00:21:07.060 --> 00:21:08.061
Tell me how it went.

128
00:21:10.814 --> 00:21:12.607
I do have something for you.

129
00:21:12.691 --> 00:21:13.733
She's not CIA.

130
00:21:13.817 --> 00:21:16.069
This is your
professional opinion?

131
00:21:17.070 --> 00:21:19.739
After conducting interviews
for 20 years. I can confirm it.

132
00:21:19.823 --> 00:21:21.283
Let her leave with me.

133
00:21:31.126 --> 00:21:32.126
Graciela.

134
00:21:33.211 --> 00:21:34.211
Do something for me.

135
00:21:35.547 --> 00:21:36.590
Take her and tie her up.

136
00:21:37.674 --> 00:21:39.114
Then tell everyone
we're moving out.

137
00:21:44.306 --> 00:21:45.807
We're moving out.

138
00:22:01.823 --> 00:22:04.284
We have located the rebel camp.

139
00:22:04.910 --> 00:22:06.630
Where they are holding
the American hostage.

140
00:22:08.413 --> 00:22:12.667
Now they have a second hostage.
a journalist. Violeta Matíz.

141
00:22:16.796 --> 00:22:18.236
We are going to
intercept them here.

142
00:22:19.549 --> 00:22:20.749
We are going to surround them.

143
00:22:21.509 --> 00:22:23.261
We are going to
make them desperate.

144
00:22:30.936 --> 00:22:34.189
Force them to negotiate.
to make mistakes.

145
00:22:35.106 --> 00:22:37.025
There are a lot of
eyes watching us.

146
00:22:39.694 --> 00:22:40.694
Get ready.

147
00:22:42.447 --> 00:22:43.615
Any questions?

148
00:22:46.451 --> 00:22:47.452
That's the way I like it.

149
00:22:48.370 --> 00:22:49.454
Commandos. move out!

150
00:23:32.205 --> 00:23:34.249
They're headed to the river.

151
00:23:37.168 --> 00:23:38.879
Do not engage. We're
10 minutes out.

152
00:26:58.954 --> 00:27:02.249
This is Colonel Pereira of
the Colombian National Army.

153
00:27:03.083 --> 00:27:05.710
You are completely surrounded.

154
00:27:05.794 --> 00:27:08.213
This is now my battleground.

155
00:27:09.005 --> 00:27:11.591
I decide what happens to you.

156
00:27:12.884 --> 00:27:16.638
No one will leave here alive with
Amber Chesborough or Violeta Matíz.

157
00:27:19.933 --> 00:27:22.143
You will all die
here one by one.

158
00:27:22.227 --> 00:27:24.563
Unless you release the hostages.

159
00:27:27.148 --> 00:27:28.149
I have plenty of time.

160
00:27:31.152 --> 00:27:32.153
You decide.

161
00:27:50.797 --> 00:27:52.007
I have the Comandante.

162
00:27:55.385 --> 00:27:56.386
Fire.

163
00:28:02.475 --> 00:28:04.352
We just killed your Comandante.

164
00:28:04.436 --> 00:28:05.896
It was easy.

165
00:28:10.859 --> 00:28:12.736
I can stay here indefinitely.

166
00:28:14.738 --> 00:28:16.031
For hours…

167
00:28:17.699 --> 00:28:18.700
for weeks.

168
00:28:21.202 --> 00:28:22.454
You decide.

169
00:28:55.737 --> 00:28:57.197
Make the fucking call.

170
00:30:12.439 --> 00:30:14.107
General. we have
them surrounded!

171
00:30:14.190 --> 00:30:15.775
I can capture them all!

172
00:30:16.484 --> 00:30:20.030
It doesn't matter. They
threatened to bomb more civilians.

173
00:30:20.113 --> 00:30:22.866
This comes from the top. From
the White House and the CIA.

174
00:30:22.949 --> 00:30:24.034
Do you understand?

175
00:30:24.117 --> 00:30:26.036
They don't want more
civilian casualties.

176
00:30:32.500 --> 00:30:34.211
Attention. everyone.

177
00:30:34.294 --> 00:30:36.254
Abort. abort. abort.

178
00:30:37.172 --> 00:30:38.506
Retreat.

179
00:30:38.590 --> 00:30:40.050
We're headed back to base.

180
00:32:18.106 --> 00:32:19.107
I love you.

181
00:33:33.682 --> 00:33:35.267
Trust me. Colonel.

182
00:33:35.350 --> 00:33:36.851
I know. Politics.

183
00:33:36.935 --> 00:33:40.188
But we are under a lot
of pressure to withdraw.

184
00:33:41.523 --> 00:33:42.732
It's a sad day.

185
00:33:42.816 --> 00:33:44.526
General. the day isn't over.

186
00:33:45.360 --> 00:33:47.821
It will take them 9 hours
to get to the border.

187
00:33:47.904 --> 00:33:51.575
Sir. if you can give me a bird.
we can take one more shot at this.

188
00:33:51.658 --> 00:33:54.327
The media has us
in a bad position.

189
00:33:55.787 --> 00:33:57.122
It's our country. sir.

190
00:33:57.956 --> 00:33:58.957
You're right.

191
00:33:59.040 --> 00:34:00.125
It's our country.

192
00:34:01.126 --> 00:34:02.961
I say this unofficially.

193
00:34:03.545 --> 00:34:07.007
Take volunteers and do
what you think is right.

194
00:34:13.221 --> 00:34:14.681
I need nine volunteers.

195
00:36:05.792 --> 00:36:07.252
We can cut across
the jungle by air

196
00:36:07.335 --> 00:36:08.795
and beat them to the border.

197
00:36:10.046 --> 00:36:12.173
This spot here is
the perfect ambush.

198
00:36:13.133 --> 00:36:14.259
Three guys on the ridge.

199
00:36:14.342 --> 00:36:15.594
The rest with me.

200
00:36:15.677 --> 00:36:17.012
We'll attack from the ground.
